description:
We tried out Shanghai Dumpling King a couple of weeks back, and then went back to Kingdom of Dumplings to compare the two while our taste bud memories were fresh.  

So here is the verdict:
SDK has a more varied menu (the non-dumpling dishes were ok, not great).  IF you are with a group and want variety, SDK may be the better one of the two places;
BUT I really really believe that the dumplings are much better at KoD.  The wrappers taste more al-dente and the fillings are tastier;
So if you want mostly dumplings and maybe a couple of side dishes, go to KoD;
If you don't want dumplings at all, then go to Koi Palace or K&G Lounge :)
